[[Image:Aebnistettenflue entlebuch 03.JPG|thumb|right|250px|View from Finsterwald]]
The '''Entlebuch Biosphere''' is a [[natural reserve]] at the foot of the [[Swiss Alps|Alps]], and includes the 395&nbsp;km² valley of the [[Kleine Emme|Little Emme River]] between [[Bern]] and [[Lucerne]] in the [[Switzerland|Swiss]] [[Canton of Lucerne]].
In September 2001, the region became the second [[UNESCO Biosphere Reserve]] in Switzerland, after the [[Swiss National Park]].
