[[File:SolarGIS-Solar-map-Albania-en.png|thumb|Solar radiation map of Albania]]
'''Solar power in Albania''' is widely available, but not yet developed.<ref>[http://www.ebrdrenewables.com/sites/renew/countries/Albania/default.aspx Albania] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120718074831/http://www.ebrdrenewables.com/sites/renew/countries/Albania/default.aspx |date=July 18, 2012 }}</ref> All of [[Albania]]'s electricity comes from [[hydroelectricity]]. A program to install solar water heating intended to use $2.75 million to install 75,000 m² of solar panels.<ref>[http://www.energy-community.org/pls/portal/docs/324187.PDF Renewable Energies Albania] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304025400/http://www.energy-community.org/pls/portal/docs/324187.PDF |date=2012-03-04 }}</ref> By the end of 2010 a total of 52,000 m² had been installed, with an additional 50,000 m² expected by 2015. The number of sunshine hours in Albania ranges from 2100 to 2700.<ref>[http://aea-al.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/RENEWABLE-ENERGY-ALBANIA.pdf Renewable Energy Resources and Energy Efficiency in Albania]</ref>

